    "type": "message",
    "text": "Yeah, it appears logicians and philosophers use the term \"schema\" too. However, the meaning in psychology seems to be the closest to the meaning in database theory.\n\nThe term \"program schema\" was <https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/321203.321204|seemingly coined in 1958>. It means something similar to \"pseudo-code\" or perhaps an AST. I'm not sure if this usage eventually morphed into what we know as \"database schemas\", or if it is just coincidence.",
