    "client_msg_id": "4ab62916-ad6f-49d6-afa9-ac00a0fbe4e7",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Now I thought of Markov chains describing the path of passwords... it made me laugh. An important property is \" The stationary distribution of a Markov chain describes the distribution of Xt after a sufficiently long time that the distribution of Xt does not change any longer. \" It's when the chain forgets its initial conditions. For a password this is when it has reached the darknet and haveibeenpwned! It's doesn't matter about your security, all passwords will eventually reach this state regardless of which database you originally store it in!",
    "user": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
    "ts": "1645338631.027139",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
