    "client_msg_id": "d663f26c-5180-4001-b86f-1edced699ee8",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "A very good thread, thanks for the pointer. I couldn't stop myself from jumping in :wink: I have been thinking in this space as well for a long time, though contrary to <@U016VUZGUUQ>, I am not out to unify the two branches, but to exploit their complementarity. One reason is that I see the two branches as much more fundamental than their manfestation in software. For example, the experiment/theory distinction in science is very similar. Experiment explores the \"existing hardware\" of nature, whereas theory builds model to reason about nature.",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1645345216.690779",
